    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1968-11-02T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1968-11-02T09:00:00-05:00" n="180"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d180">
                <head>180. Notes of Meeting<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d180fn1">Source:
                            <persName corresp="#p_JLB1">Johnson</persName> Library, <persName
                            corresp="#p_EGM1">George M. Elsey</persName> Papers, Van De Mark
                        Transcripts [1 of 2]. No classification marking. This meeting was a regular
                        meeting of <persName corresp="#p_CCM1">Clifford</persName>’s “0830 Group” of
                        senior Defense Department officials. There is no list of
                        participants.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1968-11-02T09:00:00-05:00">November 2, 1968, 9 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_CMC1">CMC</gloss> … goes to Saigon situation analysis of
                        <persName corresp="#p_NVT1">Thieu</persName>—<gloss target="#t_CMC1"
                        >CMC</gloss> reviews, <gloss target="#t_SVN1">SVN</gloss>—He can’t
                    understand why <persName corresp="#p_NVT1">Thieu</persName> is so
                    double-crossing &amp; walks away from our agreement.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_NPH1">Nitze</persName> says it’s clear as day! <persName
                        corresp="#p_NVT1">Thieu</persName> is scared that <persName
                        corresp="#p_HHH1">Humphrey</persName> &amp; Democrats will force a coalition
                    on him &amp; the Republicans won’t &amp; he’s <hi rend="italic">sure</hi> this
                    is an <gloss target="#t_LBJ1">LBJ</gloss> plot at the dying hours of the
                    Admins.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_CMC1">CMC</gloss> argues at length (to convince himself) that
                    we are right &amp; that <persName corresp="#p_NVT1">Thieu</persName> has no
                    basis for double-crossing <gloss target="#t_LBJ1">LBJ</gloss> &amp; walking away
                    from the agreed-upon position of S.V.Nam participation at Paris.</p>
                <pb facs="0556" n="522" xml:id="pg_522"/>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_NPH1">Nitze</persName> keeps trying—in vain—to get <gloss
                        target="#t_CMC1">CMC</gloss> to see that there is a rational explanation for
                        <persName corresp="#p_NVT1">Thieu</persName>’s behavior.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_NPH1">Nitze</persName> pointed out the fact that their
                    prior agreement probably didn’t mean anything, because they never thought Hanoi
                    would agree to their going to Paris anyway &amp; so it was lip service.</p>
                <p>(The longer <gloss target="#t_CMC1">CMC</gloss> talks the madder he gets at
                    S.V.Nam—he’s disgusted &amp; ready to dump <gloss target="#t_SVN1"
                    >SVN</gloss>am. “Screw You” is all he says he’d tell them.)</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_CMC1">CMC</gloss> now gets blunt—<persName corresp="#p_TM1"
                        >Max Taylor</persName> &amp; <persName corresp="#p_RD1">Rusk</persName>
                    &amp; <persName corresp="#p_RWW1">Rostow</persName> have an enormous personal
                    stake in seeing a “beautiful democracy” there; they’re committed so to <gloss
                        target="#t_SVN1">SVN</gloss>am they’d let Saigon run the whole show for
                    us.</p>
                <p>At Kay Graham’s house last night Reston, Geyelin, Joe Kraft, Joe Alsop<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d180fn2">Publisher of the <hi rend="italic">Washington Post</hi>
                        Katharine Graham, <hi rend="italic">The New York Times</hi> columnist
                            <persName>James Reston</persName>, reporter <persName>Philip
                            Geyelin</persName> of the <hi rend="italic">Washington Post</hi>,
                        syndicated columnist <persName>Joseph Kraft</persName>, and syndicated
                        columnist <persName>Joseph Alsop</persName>.</note> tried to get <gloss
                        target="#t_CMC1">CMC</gloss> to describe the ultimate “political
                    settlement”. He said that’s their (<gloss target="#t_SVN1">SVN</gloss>’s) job;
                    we’re interested only in getting war over with.</p>
                <p>We all agree that S.V.Nam attitude will change after next Wed.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d180fn3">November 6.</note> election results are in.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_CMC1">CMC</gloss>: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I do not believe we ought to be in V Nam</p>
                        <p>“I think our being there is a mistake</p>
                        <p>“This demonstrates <hi rend="italic">to me</hi> why I think it was a
                            calamity”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_NPH1">Nitze</persName>—I thought it was a mistake in 65
                    &amp; I said so, but that’s irrelevant history. But we <hi rend="italic"
                        >are</hi> there &amp; we have had 29,000 men killed &amp; we have a military
                    success &amp; now I don’t want to throw it away by angry, ill-chosen
                    reactions!</p>
                <p>Long philosophical discourse <gloss target="#t_CMC1">CMC</gloss> + <gloss
                        target="#t_PHN1">PHN</gloss> re why we’re there &amp; what kind of an
                    outcome.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_PHN1">PHN</gloss> says he thinks we can negotiate North V Nam
                    out of S.V.Nam.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_CMC1">CMC</gloss> disgusted, he says, with it all.</p>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion of arms sales to Israel.]</p>
            </div>
